Stuart Martin And Leon Levy, Took our profile On February 12 2025 At moosehead Beach. We started getting things ready at two o'clock And low tide was that 226 PM. The profile direction was Southeast 150 degrees And it was a beautiful sunny day Winds where 4.3 and Gus were 4.7 and the temperature was minus six Celsius. The upper part of the beach was partially covered with snow And there was no vegetation showing. The brook on the end of the beach Had changed direction from last month And it was coming straight out into the ocean. There was a few piles of peat moss Along the top part of the beach On the other side of the brook And Going down along the top side of the beach. It was a full moon That evening And the tide was quite low. We finished our profile at about 3 P.M And then We proceed it to go up to Leon's And do the measurements on his beech. We finished his beech Approximately 3 P.m Um Wednesday afternoon Our hands we're getting pretty cold And We called it a day.
